  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH Assistance to IDPs in Aleppo, Hama, and Idleb Governorates</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Relief International&apos;s (RI) project addresses the immediate water,sanitation.and hygiene (WASH) needs of extremely vulnerable community members and internally displaced persons (IPOs) in Aleppo, Hama and ldleb Governorates who are affected by escalating violence. Based on the changing situation, Rl aims to deliver emergency WASH services to meet the emerging WASH needs in Aleppo, Hama and ldleb Governorates as a result of the changing security and conflict dynamics. While ensuring Rl&#x2019;s prepositioning supplies to respond to a possible cholera outbreak in all Governorates. Rl Turkey is requesting support from HPF to provide comprehensive WASH support, which would serve an estimated 59,000 internally displaced persons (lDPs) and host community members. This support will include: emergency water trucking, water storage (through household storage Jerry cans and larger household storage where possible), Aquatab or other chlorine distribution where water networks and pumping stations are intact, water quality monitoring, hygiene promotion, assessment and data collection on WASH needs and gaps in service provision, emergency sanitation activities, and a cash/Voucher program to support ongoing WASH needs (including dignity and hygiene items for women and children) where possible in Aleppo, Hama,and ldleb Governorates.</narrative>
  </description>
